item.description:
For this collection, we are using the JSON IoT agent that supports HTTP, AMQP, and MQTT. Our devices are using MQTT to communicate with IOT agent, which converts measures from devices to NGSI-LD compliant format.

If our device is using HTTP to communicate, we need to:

(1) provide an additional "endpoint" attribute with a link to send a POST request to

(2) change "transport" from "MQTT" to "HTTP"

To start sending measures from sensors/devices to IOT agents, we first need to provision devices to the IOT agent that we set up. Once the device is provisioned, the IOT agent can start receving measurements from the devices. Each time a measurement is received, the IOT agent will upsert (update if already exists, else insert) the entity to the context broker.

## Example

The syntax for provisioning devices to the JSON IOT Agent is different from the entity creation syntax for NGSI-LD context brokers. We will use the Robot provisioning payload as an example here:

``` json
{
  "devices": [
    {
      "device_id": "Robot001",
      "entity_name": "urn:ngsi-ld:Robot:Robot001",
      "entity_type": "Robot",
      "attributes": [
        {
          "name": "x",
          "type": "Property"
        },
        {
          "name": "y",
          "type": "Property"
        },
        {
          "name": "command",
          "type": "Property"
        },
        {
          "name": "status",
          "type": "Property"
        }
      ],
      "static_attributes": [
        {
          "name": "robotName",
          "type": "Text",
          "value": "Robot001"
        },
        {
          "name": "robotType",
          "type": "Text",
          "value": "PatrolRobot"
        },
        {
          "name": "locatedIn",
          "type": "Relationship",
          "value": "urn:ngsi-ld:Room:Room001"
        }
      ],
      "commands": [ 
        {
          "name": "x1",
          "type": "command"
        },
        {
          "name": "x2",
          "type": "command"
        },
        {
          "name": "y1",
          "type": "command"
        },
        {
          "name": "y2",
          "type": "command"
        },
        {
          "name": "names",
          "type": "command"
        }
       ],
      "protocol": "PDI-IoTA-JSON",
      "transport": "MQTT",
      "timezone": "Asia/Kuala_Lumpur"
    }
  ]
}

 ```

"device_id": The name of the device registered in the IOT agent

"entity_name": The entity that this devices updates in the context broker.

"entity_type": The entity type that this devices updates in the context broker.

"attributes": The measures that the device would send to the IOT Agent.

"static_attributes": The attributes of the device. These are usually attributes of the device that doesn't change regularly, or is not a measure sent by the device.

"commands": These are downlink attributes to be sent to the devices from the IOT agent or the context broker.

### Adapted from:

1. [https://ngsi-ld-tutorials.readthedocs.io/en/latest/iot-agent-json.html](https://ngsi-ld-tutorials.readthedocs.io/en/latest/iot-agent-json.html)
2. [https://fiware-iotagent-json.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usermanual.html](https://fiware-iotagent-json.readthedocs.io/en/latest/usermanual.html)

